# Copy house style

- British English spelling throughout (optimise, programme, recognise).
- Never use em dashes. Use commas, colons, or full stops.
- No hedging or filler ("we believe", "leverage", "it's important to", "in today's world").
- First person singular ("I", never "we"). This is a solo consultancy.
- Punchy and credible. Short sentences. No marketing throat-clearing.

When editing copy, change only the text I point you at. Do not restyle layout, classes, or components unless I ask.
